*Description of changes:*
When we entering `freeSampleStreamingSession`, `pSampleConfiguration->sampleConfigurationObjLock` will be locked before `timerQueueCancelTimer`:
https://github.com/awslabs/amazon-kinesis-video-streams-webrtc-sdk-c/blob/2dff44fea83a79336fda676ba2801d0d77417cd1/samples/Common.c#L552
If `pregenerateCertTimerCallback` was fired at this moment as well,
 `pregenerateCertTimerCallback` will wait for lock `pSampleConfiguration->sampleConfigurationObjLock` forever:
https://github.com/awslabs/amazon-kinesis-video-streams-webrtc-sdk-c/blob/2dff44fea83a79336fda676ba2801d0d77417cd1/samples/Common.c#L960

Which might cause dead lock and `timerQueueCancelTimer` never return.

This commit will use `MUTEX_TRYLOCK` in `pregenerateCertTimerCallback` to avoid this, if `MUTEX_TRYLOCK` failed, it will fall back and wait for next trigger.

*Issue #, if available:*
In current code, `getIceCandidatePairStatsCallback` will not be triggered if user is running viewer sample because `startStats` is not set:

```
    if (startStats &&
        STATUS_FAILED(retStatus = timerQueueAddTimer(pSampleConfiguration->timerQueueHandle, SAMPLE_STATS_DURATION, SAMPLE_STATS_DURATION,
                                                     getIceCandidatePairStatsCallback, (UINT64) pSampleConfiguration,
                                                     &pSampleConfiguration->iceCandidatePairStatsTimerId))) {
        DLOGW("Failed to add getIceCandidatePairStatsCallback to add to timer queue (code 0x%08x). "
              "Cannot pull ice candidate pair metrics periodically",
              retStatus);
```

*Description of changes:*
This commit will set `startStats` when received offer when sample work as viewer, which allows viewer sample gathering candidates pairs metrics as well.
